  <fr:p>Let <fr:tex>I\subseteq  A</fr:tex> be a directed subset such that <fr:tex>\bigsqcup {I}</fr:tex> is positive; we must find a positive element of <fr:tex>I</fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-0023.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-0023">positively generated</fr:link> we know that <fr:tex>\bigsqcup {I} \sqsubseteq  \bigsqcup {\mathopen {}\left (I\cap  A^+\right )\mathclose {}}</fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex>\bigsqcup {I}</fr:tex> is positive and <fr:tex>I\cap  A^+</fr:tex> <fr:link
href="jms-0028.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-0028">is semidirected</fr:link>, it follows that the latter is inhabited.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
